The as-synthesized NIR-CDs can be used to detect H2S. The detection conditions including pH and reaction time were optimized (provided in Supplementary material). The fluorescence intensity of the NIR-CDs at 683 nm decreases regularly with increasing concentration of NaHS, as shown in Fig. 5
                        a. Fig. 5b presents a good linear relationship between F/F0 (F0 and F are the fluorescence intensities of NIR-CDs at 683 nm before and after adding NaHS, respectively) and the NaHS concentration of 0.5−20 μM (R2 = 0.9981). The estimated limit of detection (LOD) for H2S is 56 nM with a signal-to-noise of 3, suggesting that NIR-CDs have a good sensitivity to H2S. In addition, the performance of the NIR-CDs with other previously reported H2S probes based on different materials was compared detailedly (Table 1
                        ). The emission wavelength and response time of our near-infrared probe are superior to those of previously reported materials, and LOD is comparable to these reports.
